Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Slice the @Wheat Demi-Baguette{1} into ¾-inch cubes. Toss the cubes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Place in the oven to toast ~{6-8%minutes}, or until golden brown on the outside but still slightly soft on the inside.

Wash and dry all produce. Meanwhile, halve, pit, and thinly slice the @Nectarine{1}(halved and thinly sliced). Halve, peel, and mince the @Shallot{1}(halved, peeled, and minced). Using a #vegetable peeler{}, shave the @Zucchini{1} into ribbons lengthwise, rotating as necessary. Discard the seedy center. Place the zucchini ribbons in a #large bowl{} and store in the fridge to chill.

Prep remaining ingredients: Remove the bread cubes from the oven to cool. Slice the @Fresh Mozzarella{4%ounce} into ½-inch cubes.

> TIP: We sent extra. Save 1/4 for another recipe.

Thinly slice the @Mint{1/4%ounce}(thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season the @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} on all sides with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Add the chicken to the pan and cook ~{5-6%minutes} per side, until cooked through. Set aside for ~{5%minutes}, then dice into cubes.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the shallot, @White Wine Vinegar{2%tablespoon}, and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} (to taste). Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> TIP: If you're not a big fan of raw onion, use less shallot.

Finish: Toss the mozzarella, bread cubes, chicken, mint, @Arugula{2%ounce}, nectarine, and vinaigrette into the #bowl{} with the zucchini ribbons. Season generously with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Finish with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, if desired. Divide between bowls and enjoy!